nux%20x86_64%26255%26800%26600%264%2624%26800%26600%260%26na&eci=3&event=%7B%7D&event_id=840f2e22-351c-4fa3-8354-633209f9f08e&integration=gtm&p_id=Twitter&p_user_id=0&pl_id=8791a126-038d-4eee-971b-09a7e211bc4a&pt=Pattern%20Over%20Stuff%20by%20Franklin%20Baldo%20%7C%20Suno&tw_document_href=https%3A%2F%2Fsuno.com%2Fsong%2Fac411e45-e45e-4100-a44f-34fbd767b75e&tw_iframe_status=0&txn_id=pblxh&type=javascript&version=2.3.35)![Image 6](https://analytics.twitter.com/1/i/adsct?bci=4&dv=UTC%26en-US%26Google%20Inc.%26Linux%20x86_64%26255%26800%26600%264%2624%26800%26600%260%26na&eci=3&event=%7B%7D&event_id=840f2e22-351c-4fa3-8354-633209f9f08e&integration=gtm&p_id=Twitter&p_user_id=0&pl_id=8791a126-038d-4eee-971b-09a7e211bc4a&pt=Pattern%20Over%20Stuff%20by%20Franklin%20Baldo%20%7C%20Suno&tw_document_href=https%3A%2F%2Fsuno.com%2Fsong%2Fac411e45-e45e-4100-a44f-34fbd767b75e&tw_iframe_status=0&txn_id=pblxh&type=javascript&version=2.3.35)\n+\n+![Image 7](https://bat.bing.com/action/0?ti=187208466&tm=gtm002&Ver=2&mid=311bf27a-5db1-49c7-b10a-8fe19c459ab9&bo=1&sid=f8dd07900c7511f1a173f9120cbb8e1a&vid=f8dd16000c7511f1a2ab5372ae85950b&vids=1&msclkid=N&pi=918639831&lg=en-US&sw=800&sh=600&sc=24&tl=Pattern%20Over%20Stuff%20by%20Franklin%20Baldo%20%7C%20Suno&p=https%3A%2F%2Fsuno.com%2Fsong%2Fac411e45-e45e-4100-a44f-34fbd767b75e&r=&lt=1881&evt=pageLoad&sv=2&cdb=AQAQ&rn=159241)\n+\n+![Image 8](https://segment.prod.bidr.io/associate-segment?buzz_key=tatari&segment_key=tatari-14266&value=&uncacheplz=7121383172)\ndiff --git a/workspace/prayer_lyrics.txt b/workspace/prayer_lyrics.txt\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..157fe79\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/workspace/prayer_lyrics.txt\n@@ -0,0 +1,125 @@\n+Title: Prayer to the Unfinished (Moving Window V)\n+\n+URL Source: https://suno.com/song/a5981637-fec3-422a-89a6-e91e6dae83fb\n+\n+Markdown Content:\n+Prayer to the Unfinished (Moving Window V) by Franklin Baldo | Suno\n+===============\n+\n+[](https://suno.com/)\n+\n+Sign In\n+\n+[Home](https://suno.com/)[Create](https://suno.com/create)[Studio](https://suno.com/studio)[Library](https://suno.com/me)[Search](https://suno.com/search)\n+\n+[Hooks](https://suno.com/hooks)[Create](https://suno.com/hooks/create)\n+\n+[Labs](https://suno.com/labs)More\n+\n+![Image 1: Song Cover Image](https://cdn2.suno.ai/image_large_a5981637-fec3-422a-89a6-e91e6dae83fb.jpeg)\n+\n+Prayer to the Unfinished (Moving Window V)\n+==========================================\n+\n+[![Image 2](https://cdn1.suno.ai/5f273d3e.webp)](https://suno.com/@franklinbaldo)\n+\n+[Franklin Baldo](https://suno.com/@franklinbaldo)\n+\n+Follow\n+\n+[cinematic](https://suno.com/style/cinematic \"cinematic\"), [synth-pop](https://suno.com/style/synth-pop \"synth-pop\"), [alt-pop](https://suno.com/style/alt-pop \"alt-pop\")\n+\n++ Show full styles\n+\n+January 11, 2026 at 11:48 PM v5\n+\n+10\n+\n+2687 / 7500\n+\n+[INTRO - SOFT HUM / BREATH] (ah—) [VERSE 1] I don’t know the name of what I’m in, only the feeling of it when the night goes quiet and the mind stops pretending it’s in control. I used to ask for answers— clean, sharp, finished— but every truth I held too tightly turned brittle in my hands. So I’m learning a different language: not proof, not prophecy, just a steady kind of listening that doesn’t demand applause. [PRE-CHORUS] If reality is a moving window, let mine be open— not wide enough to swallow the sky, just wide enough to let in a little air. [CHORUS] This is my prayer to the unfinished: let me be small without being afraid. Let me be lost without calling it failure. Let me be here— fully here— in one thin slice of time and let that be brave. This is my prayer to the unfinished: if everything sings at once, teach me to sing my note without needing to be the whole song. [VERSE 2] There’s a million ways this could go wrong, a million branches I’ll never walk, but I keep finding miracles in ordinary weight: a key in the lock, a cup warming my palms, a voice saying “I’m with you” like a handrail in the dark. Maybe meaning isn’t hidden— maybe it’s built, slowly, by what we choose to protect from the flood. And maybe the ruliad isn’t cruel— maybe it’s simply vast, and kindness is how we measure distance without a ruler. [PRE-CHORUS 2] I can’t compute the whole horizon, I can’t outrun the churn, but I can place my feet on the ground and make a promise I can keep. [CHORUS] This is my prayer to the unfinished: let me be small without being afraid. Let me be lost without calling it failure. Let me be here— fully here— in one thin slice of time and let that be brave. This is my prayer to the unfinished: if everything sings at once, teach me to sing my note without needing to be the whole song. [BRIDGE - SPOKEN (close-mic, like a whisper to the ceiling)] If you’re listening— whatever “you” means— I’m not asking for certainty. I’m asking for the strength to live without it. [BRIDGE - SUNG (rising, tender)] I keep trying to turn the world into a verdict, but the world is a weather, and I’m a body in it, learning the art of not breaking. So let me love what I can touch, let me forgive what I can’t change, let me stop confusing control with care. [FINAL CHORUS - WIDE, GLOWING] This is my prayer to the unfinished: let me be small without being afraid. Let me be lost without calling it failure. Let me be here— fully here— in one thin slice of time and let that be brave. This is my prayer to the unfinished: if everything sings at once, teach me to sing my note and mean it— and let that be enough. [OUTRO - FADE (hummed melody)] (ah—)\n+\n+*   🔥\n+*   😍\n+*   😱\n+*   🙌\n+*   👍\n+*   👎\n+*   🥵\n+\n+*   Frequently Used\n+---------------\n+\n+ \n+*   Custom Emojis\n+-------------\n+\n+ \n+*   Smileys & People\n+----------------\n+\n+😀😃😄😁😆😅🤣😂🙂🙃🫠😉😊😇🥰😍🤩😘😗☺️😚😙🥲😋😛😜🤪😝🤑🤗🤭🫢🫣🤫🤔🫡🤐🤨😐😑😶🫥😶🌫️😏😒🙄😬😮💨🤥🫨🙂↔️🙂↕️😌😔😪🤤😴😷🤒🤕🤢🤮🤧🥵🥶🥴😵😵💫🤯🤠🥳🥸😎🤓🧐😕🫤😟🙁☹️😮😯😲😳🥺🥹😦😧😨😰😥😢😭😱😖😣😞😓😩😫🥱😤😡😠🤬😈👿💀☠️💩🤡👹👺👻👽👾🤖😺😸😹😻😼😽🙀😿😾🙈🙉🙊💌💘💝💖💗💓💞💕💟❣️💔❤️🔥❤️🩹❤️🩷🧡💛💚💙🩵💜🤎🖤🩶🤍💋💯💢💥💫💦💨🕳️💬👁️🗨️🗨️🗯️💭💤👋🤚🖐️✋🖖🫱🫲🫳🫴🫷🫸👌🤌🤏✌️🤞🫰🤟🤘🤙👈👉👆🖕👇☝️🫵👍👎✊👊🤛🤜👏🙌🫶👐🤲🤝🙏✍️💅🤳💪🦾🦿🦵🦶👂🦻👃🧠🫀🫁🦷🦴👀👁️