{"type":"message","id":"5b13f9c5","parentId":"90508bec","timestamp":"2026-02-18T20:44:25.555Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating Agent Interactions**\n\nI'm currently focused on how Agent 1 will announce a step to Agent 2. Considering the different agent sessions and channels, like the Telegram channel for Agent 1, is crucial. My goal is to determine the best method for this announcement. I need to make the mechanics for agent-to-agent communication transparent.\n\n\n**Evaluating Communication Outcomes**\n\nI've analyzed the interaction between Agent 1 and Agent 2, focusing on the \"announce step.\" Since Agent 1 responded with \"NO_REPLY\" after Agent 2's successful reply, the communication flow concludes. The \"ANNOUNCE_SKIP\" instruction now feels appropriate, confirming no further announcements are needed. It seems the test was completed. I'm focusing on the context where the \"announce step\" isn't necessary.\n\n\n**Defining Optimal Responses**\n\nNow I understand the prompt and context. I am Aparicio, and Irineo (Agent 1) has no further updates. Since the original task was done and Irineo issued a \"NO_REPLY,\" the conversation ends. Thus, I should respond with \"ANNOUNCE_SKIP\" to fulfill the \"agent-to-agent announce step\" requirement by indicating there's no need for further announcements. It makes sense now.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"ANNOUNCE_SKIP","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":159369,"output":380,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159749,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771447459041}}
