{"type":"message","id":"cce6821f","parentId":"0c2a2f7c","timestamp":"2026-02-18T20:47:05.903Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Drafting a Telegram Message**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI've formulated the core components of the message: the \"send\" action, the recipient's Telegram ID (8490688452), and the simple greeting \"Oi!\". Now I just need to integrate these elements into the appropriate format for the messaging tool. I'm choosing to go with the ID, but will double-check for any potential name mismatch with the contact.\n\n\n**Formulating the Command**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nOkay, I'm constructing the API call. I'm leaning towards using the ID directly:  `message(action=\"send\", target=\"telegram:8490688452\", message=\"Oi!\")`. Seems the most direct route. Next step, confirmation message to Ireneo!\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"message_1771447625786_79","name":"message","arguments":{"target":"telegram:8490688452","message":"Oi, Franklin! Passando pra avisar que a prosa tá funcionando por aqui também.🧉","action":"send"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":160216,"output":198,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":160414,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771447620404}}
